                | #[m \deg(f) = n^2]
            p
                | Each of #[m 0,1,\infty] has #[m n ] preimages in #[m F_n(\overline \QQ)].

        p
            | The idea now is that #[m N(A,B, C)] is measuring ramification, while #[m H(A, B,C)] is a height function.
